NewsBreak: U.S. Oil Inventories Fell by 1.7M Last Week – EIA

Commodities 25 minutes ago (Oct 24, 2019 01:46)

© Reuters. Investing.com - Inventories of unexpectedly fell in the latest week, the Energy Information Administration said Wednesday, sending oil prices higher in morning trading. fell by about 1.7 million barrels for the week ended Oct.18. Analysts expected a rise of about 2.23 million barrels, according to forecasts compiled by Investing.com. fell by 3.1 million barrels, compared with an expected drop of 2.27 million barrels. dropped by about 2.72 million barrels, versus forecasts for a decline of about 2.8 million barrels. rose 0.8% to $54.92 following the report. They were around $54.55 just before the release of the numbers.
